.TH "vmw_du_crtc_reset" 9 "vmw_du_crtc_reset" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_du_crtc_reset \- creates a blank vmw crtc state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_du_crtc_reset
.BI "(struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc" 12
DRM crtc
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Resets the atomic state for \fIcrtc\fP by freeing the state pointer (which
might be NULL, e.g. at driver load time) and allocating a new empty state
object.
